verbose_text: The common prognostic covariates were age of disease onset, sex, nodal status with ECS, degree of differentiation, T status, LND, sole preoperative serum CRP and SCC-Ag levels, tumor depth, and combined preoperative serum CRP-SCC-Ag levels, all of which were collected to investigate their prognostic significance for 5-year DFS and OS through UVA and MVA.
